 # Phase 3: Priority
 
-Add priority support to tasks.
-
-## Updated Methods
-
-- **`enqueue(queueName, payload, options?)`** - The options object can include `priority`.
-  - `priority`: number from 1 (highest) to 10 (lowest). Default is 5.
+Add priority support so that more urgent tasks are processed before less urgent ones.
 
 ## Requirements
 
-- `dequeue()` returns the highest priority task first (lowest number = highest priority)
-- Within the same priority level, FIFO order is preserved
-- Default priority is 5 if not specified
-- Priority values outside 1-10 should throw an error
-- Priority is per-queue (each named queue has its own priority ordering)
-- The task object should include a `priority` property
+- Tasks can be assigned a priority level from 1 (highest) to 10 (lowest). The default priority is 5.
+- When retrieving the next task, higher-priority tasks (lower number) are returned first.
+- Tasks with the same priority are returned in FIFO order.
+- Invalid priority values (outside 1-10) should cause an error.
+- Priority operates per-queue -- each named queue maintains its own priority ordering.
+- The task object should expose its priority level.
